    <note>Huang(2) Qi(3) [25600] This is an interesting case study in the interlocking marriages that tied several branches of a common root lineage together. Qi(3)'s wife, born Lu(5) was a descendant of a branch of the Wujun Lu(5) who moved to Huzhou at the same time that Lu You's ancestors moved to Shaoxing. Qi(3)'s son-in-law was a nephew of Lu(5) You, whereas Qi(3)'s probable nephew, Shufeng [20550], was a son-in-law of the Jinqi county Lu(5). Lu You, WJ, 37.7a-7b (wife, born Lu(5), who died in 1200 at age 67). CBD mistakes this Huang(2) Qi(3) for a Guilin Huang(2) Qi (not in dataset). CBD, 4, 2863-4.</note>
